ade farmer. Cleared land and built a log cabin upon arrival in Addison County VT about 1800. Owned 500 acres at the time of his death in 1833. The homestead was inherited by his son Hiram Norton."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["vermont_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"migration","header":"Cleared Vermont homestead at age twenty-three","body":"Abel Norton was born in Connecticut in 1777 and migrated to Addison County, Vermont about 1800. He cleared land, built a log cabin, and farmed there the rest of his life. By his 1833 death he owned five hundred acres and was called in the local history 'a self-made man.' His son Hiram inherited the homestead."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Raised ten children eight survived to adulthood","body":"Abel and Mehitable raised ten children at the Vermont homestead. Per the 19th-century Addison County local history, eight of the ten survived to adulthood — a high rate for the early-1800s frontier. Two children are presently identified: Calvin and Hiram."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"abel-norton-1777"},"HD3479":{"id":"HD3479","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Calvin","last_name":"Norton","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Calvin Norton"},"birth":{"year":1811,"month":3,"day":10,"city":"Weybridge","county":"Addison","state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{},"residence":{"city":"Weybridge","county":"Addison","state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":7,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"H01043","mother_id":"X02553"},"number_of_marriages":2,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"X02566","date_year":1835,"date_month":10,"date_day":8,"location_county":"Addison","location_state":"Vermont","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1884,"children_ids":["HD3480"]},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"X02567","date_year":1885,"date_month":3,"date_day":19,"location_county":"Addison","location_state":"Vermont","location_country":"United States","children_ids":[]}],"education":[],"career":[{"role":"Farmer","location":"Essex County, New York","end_year":1847,"notes":"Purchased a farm in Essex County NY where he remained twelve years."},{"role":"Farmer","organization":"Goodale farm","location":"Addison County, Vermont","start_year":1847,"end_year":1854,"notes":"Returned to Addison County VT in 1847 and purchased the Goodale farm — 166 acres with a residence built by Jared Goodale at an early date."},{"role":"Farmer","organization":"Lawrence place","location":"Weybridge, Addison County, Vermont","start_year":1854,"notes":"Moved to Weybridge VT in 1854 and bought the Lawrence place — 50 acres. Owned multiple farms in Addison County aggregating more than 500 acres."}],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"career","header":"Owned five hundred acres across Addison County","body":"Calvin Norton spent his life consolidating Vermont farmland. He bought a farm in Essex County NY for twelve years; in 1847 bought the 166-acre Goodale farm in Addison County; in 1854 moved to Weybridge and bought the 50-acre Lawrence place. At peak he owned over five hundred acres across multiple Addison County farms — matching the size of his father Abel's original homestead."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Remarried at seventy-three to Jane's birthday","body":"Calvin's first wife Sarah Sargeant died November 1884 after forty-nine years of marriage. Four months later, on March 19, 1885 — Jane Sargent's forty-third birthday — Calvin married her, daughter of Samuel Sargent of Middlebury. Calvin was seventy-three; Jane was thirty years his junior."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Three children only Calvin Jr survived","body":"Calvin and Sarah Sargeant had three children — one daughter and two sons. Only the youngest son, Calvin Junior, survived to adulthood. The local history does not name the two children who died young."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"calvin-norton-1811"},"X02566":{"id":"X02566","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Sarah","last_name":"Norton","maiden_name":"Sargeant","married_names":["Norton"],"extra_names":"Surname also given as Sargent in some records","gender":"female","display_name":"Sarah Sargeant Norton"},"birth":{"county":"Addison","state":"Vermont","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1884,"month":11,"country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD3479","date_year":1835,"date_month":10,"date_day":8,"location_county":"Addison","location_state":"Vermont","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1884,"children_ids":["HD3480"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspir